For installing nomad as clients:-
sudo ./script.sh # script.sh -> pre-setup scripts , run as root user

# To access dashboard service in browser:
http://<public-ip-ec2>:9002    

# To access hello-world service in browser:
http://<public-ip-ec2>:8001    


[Nomad Client]
   |
   | (reports allocation status)
   v
[Nomad Server]
   |
   | (uses Consul ACL token)
   v
[Consul] <--- ACLs checked
   |
   | (registers/deregisters services & health checks)
   v
[Consul Catalog] --- provides service discovery to jobs & systems
